RULES

About LPL

The Tencent League of Legends Pro League (LPL) is the premier League of Legends esports competition in China. The LPL features 12 teams split into two divisions of 6 teams each. Each team faces every other team inside their division twice over the course of the season, and every team outside their division once over the course of the season. All regular season matches are Best of 3. Winning a Best of 3 series counts as one win, or one point.

Tiebreakers

If two teams are tied after group stages complete, their head to head record will be the first tiebreaker.

If three or more teams are tied:

  • Number of wins among these teams will be ranked.
  • If two teams has the same relative number of wins, the head to head record in group stage between these two teams will be the tiebreaker.
  • If teams are still tied, apply the above 1 & 2 tiebreakers again(rank the number of wins and check the head to head record).
  • If teams are still tied at the third time, apply the 1 & 2 tiebreakers again (rank the number of wins and check the head to head record).
  • If teams are still tied after the above tiebreaker, the team who won its game in the shortest time against the other team during the group stage will be considered as a higher rank.
  • If this does not result in a hierarchical ranking of teams, the team who lost its game in the longest time against the other team during the group stage will be considered as a higher rank.

Playoff Format

  • The top 2 teams of each division automatically qualify for playoffs.
  • The 3rd place team of each division plays against the 4th place team of the opposite division. The winner qualifies for playoffs.
  • A 3rd/4th place match will be played
  • All matches are Best of 5.

Relegation Format

  • The 6th place teams of each division will play against each other. The winner goes to a relegation match vs. the 3rd place LSPL team, the loser is demoted to the LSPL.
  • The 5th place teams of each division will play against each other. The winner stays in the LPL, the loser goes to a relegation match vs. the 2nd place LSPL team.
  • All matches are Best of 5.

 

How to watch

You can watch the LPL live every week on lolesports or on our spoiler-free vods page once the match is finished. 

---- GLOBAL RULES

GLOBAL RULES

The Global Contract Database can be downloaded here.

INTERREGIONAL ANTI-POACHING AND ANTI-TAMPERING POLICY

 

What is the interregional anti-poaching and anti-tampering policy?

No team member or affiliate of a team may engage in the solicitation, luring, or discussion of employment of a player who is under a league-recognized contract with a professional team competing in the top-level league of a region. Similarly, players under league-recognized contracts cannot solicit or reach out directly to other team members or affiliates of other teams. In the event of prolonged discussions of employment that aren't sanctioned by the management of both teams, both the party attempting to poach and the player being poached will be subject to penalties at the discretion of league officials.

Should any interested team wish to engage in conversation with a player under a league-recognized contract with another team, they must first contact the management of the team holding the contract.

League Notification: 

After the teams have come to an agreement and before initiating contact between the interested team and player of interest, they must notify their respective regional office of the agreement, with confirmation from both teams' management via email.

Prospective teams and team affiliates (owners seeking to enter a league, etc.) attempting to poach players will also be subject to sanctions, up to and including denial of entry into Riot-sanctioned leagues and competitive events.

If I'm interested in acquiring a player, how do I know if he or she is currently under contract?

As a team, you can inquire about the availability of players - it just needs to be to the player's management so long as that player is under contract.

The database linked above contains the contract end-dates of contracted players currently participating in leagues where there are league-recognized contracts (i.e., contracts that conform with league minimum standards, such as minimum player compensation). It also includes contact information for teams who have volunteered contact information. It will be updated at the beginning of every split and periodically during the split to reflect roster modifications.

This database is intended as a resource to facilitate legitimate communication between teams and players. Where there is good reason to believe a player is under a league-recognized contract despite not being in the database (e.g. a brand new player in a league with officially-recognized contracts not yet having his or her information reflected in the database), teams are expected to contact management rather than approach players directly.

If I'm a contracted player interested in leaving my team, what are my options?

While contracted players cannot reach out to other teams' affiliates, they can:

  • Publicly state their interest in leaving their team and encourage any and all interested party to contact their management.
  • Players cannot encourage specific teams, publicly or privately, to reach out to their management.
  • Exercise a buyout clause in their contract to leave their team if one exists.
  • Reach out to teams once their contract expires (typically during the off-season for most players).

Clarification of restrictions:

  • Teams and affiliates of those teams cannot engage in discussions with players under contract regarding potential employment.
  • Teams are to reach out to other teams directly regarding employment of contracted players.
  • Players under contract with a team should not engage in employment discussion directly with other teams.
  • Players not under contract are free to reach out to potential employers and vice-versa.

Why do you have the current poaching policy?

Poaching protections are important both for the stability of organizations and to avoid competitive integrity issues. During the season, it's important that players aren't being distracted from their preparation or being tempted to play at less than 100% by offers of employment from rival teams.

When players and teams sign a contract they are entering into an agreement that a player will play for a team during a defined period of time and be duly compensated for their play - players abruptly dissolving their contracts due to employment discussions with other teams during the season creates a chaotic environment for teams and players and undermines the stability of the competitive ecosystem.

This doesn't mean that we want to prevent players from ever switching teams or finding the team that is the best fit for them - discussing the possibility of being traded to another team with their management, or simply waiting until their current contract is up before engaging in any negotiation they want. For players whose contract includes a buyout clause, that's an option they may be able to exercise as well. Ultimately, the value of contracts goes both ways. For players, contracts provide stability and the promise of a paycheck. For teams, contracts guarantee that contracted players play for their team and if a player wants to leave a team, the team management are a necessary part of that discussion. This is an important dynamic to preserve, and poaching protections are one way of doing so.

INTERREGIONAL MOVEMENT POLICY

1.2 REGIONAL RESIDENCY REQUIREMENT & WORK ELIGIBILITY

a) Resident Defined. For purposes of this Rule 1.2, a player is deemed to be a "Resident" of a region if such player has legally resided and been primarily present in such region for no less than twenty-four months out of the thirty-six months immediately prior to such players' participation in the first game of the applicable tournament (i.e., a match in the World Championship Event, LCS, or Challenger Series).

In defining a Resident, we sought to create a policy that defines Residents based on sustained and prolonged presence with a region, rather than citizenship or legal documentation. This policy makes sure that Residents not only have resided in the region whose league they wish to play in for a substantial period of time, it also gives every player the option of becoming a Resident for that league after a prolonged commitment. We used the language “primarily present” so that a reasonable amount of discretion can be used in allowing for vacations and other such temporary travel when considering eligibility.

b) Certification of Residency. All players shall certify their residency upon participation in the World Championship Event, the NA and EU LCS, and the NA and EU Challenger Series by submitting an eligibility form, and providing proof of residency as defined in Rules 1.2(c) and (d). Each team is responsible for ensuring that its players meet the residency requirements in this Rule 1.2. It shall be a violation of these Rules, by both the team and the player, if a player (or his or her parent or guardian) provides false, misleading or incomplete information resulting in the misclassification of such player’s residency and region. A violation of this Rule 1.2 by a team or a player shall also be deemed a violation of Rule 10.2, and the disciplinary measures in Rules 10.5 and 10.6 shall apply.

c) Proof of Residency. Any player over eighteen years of age may prove residency by the provision of documentary evidence sufficient to demonstrate actual residence in the region in which he or she wishes to play. Such documentary evidence may be in the form of one or more examples of:

  • i. Government Issued Documentation. A player may prove residency by providing copies of a driver’s license, voter registration form, vehicle registration, government benefits records, military or draft registration papers or other government-issued records or identification that demonstrate residency.
  • ii. Private Documentation. A player may prove residency by providing copies of school records, deeds, leases, homeowners association documents, utility bills (such as gas, water, electricity, cable, or telephone, provided that all show levels of use consistent with actual residency), bank records and statements, tax returns, insurance documents, medical records and employment records.
    •

d) Residency of Minors. Players who are below eighteen years of age may prove residency by either:

  • i. School Records. A player may prove residency by providing proof of full-time attendance at school in the region, including by providing copies of report cards, enrollment documentation, or attendance records certified by school officials; or
  • ii. Parents’ Records. A player may prove residency by (i) providing documentary evidence of the parent-child relationship, such as a birth certificate that lists the names of parents, and (ii) proof that one parent lives in the region, which may be demonstrated by provision of documentary evidence sufficient to prove residency as specified in Rule 1.2(c), above.
    •

Proving that a player has resided in a region for two out of the last three years can be a somewhat tricky process, so we’ve given categories of documentation that can help establish a player’s Resident status. This is ultimately a process that relies on making good judgment calls, but by permitting numerous categories of proof we can ensure that no player is left without options. We’ll be increasing the timeframe during which a team should submit its paperwork to register a roster change to make sure each change can be assessed within a reasonable period of time, and working with teams to collect paperwork that is acceptable for each circumstance.

e) Starters. For purposes of Rule 1.2, as stated in Rule 3.2, a "Starter" is defined as one of the five players established in the Team's starting lineup for any given game.

This part is fairly straightforward - we don’t want teams undermining the goal of this policy by keeping Residents on the bench while they play majority non-exempt non-Resident starting lineups. This rule ensures that the team actually playing is able to maintain a good balance of local and foreign talent.

f) World Championship Event. The World Championship Event is intended to bring together the best teams from each region to compete, as representatives of their region, in a global competition. In order to foster this diverse global competition, nurture regional teams, excite local and global fans, increase participation from all regions, and ensure a fair and open championship, all teams competing in the World Championship Event must meet local residency requirements. At least 60% (three out of five) Starters on any competing team must be Residents or exempt non-Residents of the region they represent in the World Championship Event. This Rule shall ensure that the goals of the World Championship Event are achieved, without undue burden on players and teams, while promoting fair play and robust competition for all participants in this global competition.

g) NA and EU LCS. The NA and EU LCS, including the NA and EU regular season and all matches leading up to the regional playoffs, are designed to identify the teams that will represent the NA and EU in the World Championship Event. In order to fulfill this mandate, all teams competing in the LCS and LCS-affiliated matches must meet the requirements in Rule 1.2(f) for teams participating in the World Championship Event, including the requirement that at least 60% (three out of five) Starters on each team be Residents of the region covered by the LCS in which they play.

h) NA and EU Challenger Series. The NA and EU Challenger Series, including the NA and EU Challenger Series regular season and all matches leading up to the Promotion Tournament, are designed to identify the teams from the NA and EU that will be promoted to the NA and EU LCS and thereby have an opportunity to represent the NA and EU in the World Championship Event. In order to fulfill this mandate, all teams competing in the Challenger Series and Challenger Series-affiliated matches must meet the requirements in Rule 1.2(f) for teams participating in the World Championship Event, including the requirement that at least 60% (three out of five) Starters on each team be Residents of the region covered by the Challenger Series in which they play.

This is the heart of the rule - having at least 3 players on every team be local to that region in some sense ensures that regional identity is preserved for a league. That principle should be reflected at every level of professional competition, from the Challenger Series all the way to representation at Worlds. Keep in mind that this specific version of the residency requirement is only going into the LCS ruleset, so it will only apply to LCS teams attending Worlds, not all Worlds-participating teams.

i) Implementation of Rule Change; Grandfathering. Any player on the Active Roster of an LCS team or a CS team who participated in the most recent Promotion Tournament at the time of this policy change who would not satisfy the Resident definition in 1.2(a) will be considered an "exempt non-resident", which allows such a player to count towards the three Residents required pursuant to Rules 1.2(f), 1.2(g), and 1.2(h). Once an exempt non-resident has met the Residency requirement, that player will be considered a Resident. A player cannot simultaneously count as a Resident for one region and as an exempt non-Resident for another region. A player can choose to waive his exempt non-Resident status in favor of counting as a Resident for another region before December 31, 11:59 pm PST 2014. In the event that a team has two or more exempt non-Resident players as Starters, they will not be permitted to add any additional non-exempt non-Residents as Starters.

This rule ensures that current LCS teams and CS teams who played in the Promotion Tournament do not have to change their rosters. In enacting the Interregional Movement Policy, it’s important to us that players already committed to playing in the region are not unduly harmed. At the same time, in the long term it’s important that changes to teams gradually move each team to a healthy balance of foreign and local talent, which is why we make the subtle distinction between Resident players and exempt non-Resident players. Allowing players to waive an exemption means that individuals who aren’t sure of the plans don’t get locked out of legitimate options. Players currently in NA can choose to waive their exemption if they would qualify as an EU resident, and vice-versa.

j) Substitutes: All teams will be required to maintain at least one Resident player as a substitute at any given time. At no point in time will teams be permitted to make a substitution which is in violation of any provision of this Rule 1.2.:

If for some reason a Starter is temporarily out of commission, we don’t want teams put in a position where they can’t field a roster in compliance with the Interregional Movement Policy. That’s why we’re requiring teams keep at least one Resident substitute on the roster as a failsafe.

k) Losing Residency: For purposes of this Rule 1.2, a player who is considered a Resident for a region will no longer be deemed to be a "Resident" of that region if such player has been primarily present in another region for 24 out of the last 36 months.

In the event that a player wants to take a break from competitive play, or has a short stint in another league that doesn’t work out, we want to make sure that they reserve the option of playing in the region where they were most recently a Resident. Giving the players the safety net of temporarily exploring options overseas without forfeiting Resident status is a priority for us, and that’s what this portion of the rule is meant to address. So, for example, an EU Resident player can join an NA team for a year, and if circumstances change and they want to go back to EU, they can do so without having lost their EU Resident status.

l) Work Eligibility: Each player must submit proof that, at the time of any LCS-affiliated match the player wishes to participate in, he/she will be (a) a legal resident of a country in their region, and (b) work-eligible in the United States (for NA players) or Germany (for EU players).

This is the same as the old residency rule: because portions of the Challenger Series and all of the LCS occur live and at a physical location, it’s important that players are present and eligible to work in the country where the event is being held.

The Interregional Movement Policy is one that benefits the overall competitive ecosystem, and other regional leagues will be incorporating something similar to the NA and EU version of the Regional Residency Requirement & Work Eligibility and releasing their equivalents at their discretion. China (LPL & LSPL), Korea (OGN The Champions, Masters & NLB), and Southeast Asia/Taiwan (GPL & LNL) handling their regional residency requirements individually. The NA and EU requirement provides a robust framework that will not only preserve regional identity in the future, but permit a healthy amount of movement between regions that is to the benefit of esports as a whole.
abouts.ko_KR:
중국 LPL 소개

텐센트 리그 오브 레전드 프로 리그(LPL)는 중국 최고의 리그 오브 레전드 e스포츠 리그입니다. LPL에는 12팀이 참가하며 6팀씩 두 조로 나뉩니다. 한 시즌 동안 조별경기는 2라운드 풀리그로 진행하며 다른 조의 팀과도 한 번씩 경기를 갖습니다. 모든 정규 시즌 경기는 3전2선승제이며 승리 팀은 승점 1점을 획득합니다.

순위 결정전

조별경기 단계 종료 후 두 팀이 같은 순위인 경우, 먼저 상대전적으로 순위를 결정합니다.

같은 순위인 팀이 세 팀 이상인 경우:

  • 승리 횟수를 기준으로 순위를 정합니다.
  • 두 팀의 상대적인 승리 횟수가 같은 경우, 조별경기 단계의 상대전적으로 순위를 결정합니다.
  • 그래도 순위를 결정할 수 없다면 위의 1번, 2번을 다시 적용합니다(즉, 승리 횟수와 상대전적 확인)
  • 3단계에서도 순위를 결정할 수 없다면 위의 1번, 2번을 다시 적용합니다(즉, 승리 횟수와 상대전적 확인)
  • 그래도 순위를 결정할 수 없다면 조별경기 단계에서 가장 최근에 같은 순위인 팀을 상대로 승리를 기록한 순으로 순위를 정합니다.
  • 여전히 순위가 같은 팀이 있다면 같은 순위인 팀을 상대로 패배한 시점이 가장 오래된 순으로 순위를 정합니다.

플레이오프 형식

  • 각 조의 1, 2위 팀은 자동으로 플레이오프에 진출합니다.
  • 각 조 3위 팀은 다른 조의 4위 팀과 대결합니다. 승자는 플레이오프에 진출합니다.
  • 3, 4위 결정전을 실시합니다.
  • 모든 경기는 5전3선승제입니다.

승강전 형식

  • 각 조의 6위 팀은 서로 대결하고 승자는 2부 리그인 LSPL 3위 팀과 승강전을 치릅니다. 패배한 팀은 LSPL로 강등됩니다.
  • 각 조의 5위 팀도 서로 대결하며 승자는 LPL에 남지만 패배한 팀은 LSPL 2위 팀과 승강전을 치릅니다.
  • 모든 경기는 5전3선승제입니다.

bios.en_US: The Bangkok Titans are the undisputed champions of Thailand’s League of Legends esports scene. They achieved six consecutive 1st place finishes in the Thailand Pro League from 2014 to 2015. However, they aren’t content with just domestic domination. The Titans have built on their foundation of success at home, climbing to 1st place finishes in both the 2015 GPL Summer and 2015 International Wildcard Tournament Turkey.
bios.fr_FR: Bangkok Titans sont les champions incontestés de la scène e-sportive thaïlandaise. Ils ont obtenu six 1re place en Thailand Pro League entre 2014 et 2015. Mais la concurrence nationale ne leur suffit pas. Les Titans ont terminé premier lors du Segment d'été de la GPL 2015 et de l'International Wildcard 2015 en Turquie.
bios.pl_PL: Bangkok Titans to niekwestionowany mistrz tajlandzkiej sceny E-sportowej League of Legends. Osiągnęło sześć 1. miejsc z rzędu w Thailand Pro League od roku 2014 do 2015. Jednakże dominacja w kraju to za mało. Titans wykorzystali sukces odniesiony w kraju, zajmując 1. miejsce w letnim GPL 2015 oraz 2015 International Wildcard Tournament Turkey.
bios.de_DE: Die Bangkok Titans sind die unangefochtenen Champions der thailändischen League of Legends eSports Szene. Sie erkämpften sich sechs Mal aufeinanderfolgend den ersten Platz in der Profi Liga zwischen 2014 und 2015. Doch trotzdem sind sie mit ihrem regionalen Erfolg nicht zufrieden. Sie knüpften an ihre Siegesreihe an und gewannen das Sommer Finale der GPL 2015 und das Wildcard Turnier in der Türkei.
bios.es_ES: Nadie puede negar que Bangkok Titans es el equipo de League of Legends más potente de Tailandia. Entre 2014 y 2015 ha obtenido seis títulos consecutivos de la Thailand Pro League. Sin embargo, no se contentan con dominar a sus anchas en su país. Los Titans han utilizado su éxito local como cimientos para crecer, como demuestra el primer puesto cosechado tanto en el torneo de verano de la GPL 2015 como en el torneo internacional por invitación celebrado en Turquía este mismo año.
bios.pt_BR: A Bangkok Titans é a campeã absoluta no League of Legends tailandês. De 2014 a 2015, eles conseguiram seis títulos na Thailand Pro League. Mas eles não estão satisfeitos com o domínio regional, e querem fazer bonito internacionalmente. O primeiro passo já foi dado: eles venceram tanto a GPL de verão 2015 quanto o International Wildcard 2015 na Turquia, conquistando a vaga para o Mundial.

bios.en_US: After barely a month of operation, the Imperium brand surprised the local scene by signing an esports division. Acquiring the best unsigned talent available, the Imperium Pro Team was formed after striking a deal with Team Exile. Since its inception, the team has shown a dominating performance in the 2014 Pro Gaming Series Winter to qualify for the Garena Premier League. After their poor performance in their first appearance in the GPL 2014 Spring Season, IPT is back stronger than ever and ready to surprise the other teams with their new strategies and talent.

The Saigon Jokers are one of SEA’s older organization. Viewers may recognize them from their appearance at the season 2 world championship, or may recognize some of their players from the 2014 All Stars challenge. While their international appearances have largely been middling, on their home court they are a much greater force to deal with. They are one of the established forces in the SEA scene, and will look to remain so this coming season.
bios.pt_BR: A Saigon Jokers é uma das organizações mais tradicionais do Sudeste Asiático. Eles podem ser lembrados por sua aparição no Mundial 2012, bem como outras em torneios Wildcard. Enquanto sua performance em palco internacional é mediana, regionalmente a equipe é uma das maiores forças. A equipe do Vietnã batalha sempre por uma vaga internacional, e está aí para provar que consegue trazer suas surpresas também para outras regiões verem.
bios.es_AR: Saigon Jokers son una de las organizaciones más viejas del Sudeste Asiático. Muchos los recuerdan por su aparición en el Mundial de la Temporada 2, o incluso por los jugadores del All-Stars 2014. Sus actuaciones internacionales no han sido destacadas, pero en su región son una potencia de temer.

bios.en_US: Having taken first place at the 2013 World Championship Chinese Regional Qualifier, Royal knows how to dominate its region. Dissatisfied with a 2nd place finish at the 2013 World Championship, Royal Club entered the season with a penchant for success and a chip on its shoulder. With high hopes for 2014, Royal Club failed to make the LPL Top 4 in the Spring, only managing 3rd in the Summer. The Royal Club that is going to the 2014 World Championship is hardly the same team, with Uzi being the only old member. However, with new blood including the Korean Lee Sin master INsec, we’ll see if Royal Club has the alchemical skill to turn silver into gold at the World Championship.

bios.fr_FR: Edward Gaming a été fondée en en 2013 dans le but de devenir la première organisation e-sport de Chine. EDG a bâti une équipe en partant de zéro dans l'espoir de s'opposer aux meilleures équipes mondiales de League of Legends. EDG a balayé la concurrence dès ses débuts en LPL pour finir en tête du championnat régional chinois en 2014. EDG entend maintenant atteindre son objectif initial, obtenir le trophée du Championnat du monde de League of Legends.
bios.pl_PL: Edward Gaming zostało założone w 2013 roku w celu utworzenia potężnej organizacji E-sportowej w Chinach. EDG utworzyło drużynę, która miała na celu rywalizację z najlepszymi drużynami League of Legends z całego świata. Nazywane „superdrużyną” EDG przebiło się przez LPL w swoim debiutanckim splicie i zostało regionalnymi mistrzami Chin w 2014 roku. Teraz EDG pragnie osiągnąć cel, do którego zostało powołane – zdobycie trofeum mistrzostw świata League of Legends.
bios.de_DE: Edward Gaming ist eine der berühmtesten chinesischen Mannschaften, die seit September 2013 in der professionellen „League of Legends“-Szene vertreten ist. Die Mannschaft feierte immer wieder Erfolge wie den Titel beim Sommer-Split der LPL 2014. Außerdem konnten sie sich mit einem 3–2 Sieg über SKT T1 im Finale des Mid-Season Invitational 2015 auch einen internationalen Titel sichern. Die Mannschaft beendete die Sommer-Saison der LPL 2015 mit 14 Siegen, 2 Niederlagen und 6 Unentschieden. Doch trotz der Erfolgreichen Geschichte der Mannschaft, konnten sie bei der Weltmeisterschaft noch kein Ausrufezeichen setzen. Dieses Mal haben sie sich jedoch gut vorbereitet und fahren mit ein paar der berühmtesten Spieler der Welt zum Turnier. Seit dem MSI wissen sie, wie sich ein Sieg auf einer internationalen Bühne anfühlt und jetzt wollen sie diesen Erfolg bei der Weltmeisterschaft wiederholen.
bios.es_ES: Edward Gaming es uno de los equipos chinos más famosos, ya que comenzó su periplo profesional en League of Legends en septiembre de 2013. Gozan de un buen historial de éxitos, entre ellos el acabar en lo más alto del split de verano de la LPL en 2014. También tienen en sus vitrinas un importante título internacional, el MSI 2015, el cual consiguieron tras ganar la final a SKT T1 por 3 a 2. El equipo obtuvo un registro de 14-2-6 en la temporada de verano de la LPL en 2015. Pero, a pesar de los éxitos que han conseguido durante su larga carrera como equipo, aún no han dejado su huella en el Mundial. Esta vez llegan a la competición preparados, con algunos de los mejores y más famosos jugadores del mundo. Ya saborearon las mieles del éxito en un escenario internacional en el MSI y ahora quieren repetir esa hazaña en el Mundial.
bios.pt_BR: A Edward Gaming é uma das mais reconhecidas equipes da China, tendo estreado no cenário profissional de League of Legends em setembro de 2013. A equipe já contabiliza vários sucessos, incluindo um primeiro lugar na Etapa de Verão da LPL em 2014. Eles também alcançaram uma grande conquista internacional com o título do Midseason Invitational 2015, batendo a SKT T1 por 3 a 2. A equipe estabeleceu um recorde de partidas de 14-2-6 na Temporada de Verão 2015 da LPL.  Apesar das conquistas ao longo da trajetória, a equipe ainda precisa deixar sua marca registrada no Mundial. Dessa vez eles entram na competição preparados e contando com alguns dos melhores e mais celebrados jogadores do mundo. Eles já sentiram o gostinho do primeiro lugar no palco internacional antes do MSI e agora estão ansiosos para repetir a dose no Mundial.
bios.es_AR:
Edward Gaming es uno de los equipos chinos más fácilmente reconocibles que por primera vez se sumó al profesionalismo de League of Legends en septiembre del 2013. El equipo tuvo su cuota de éxitos, incluido el primer lugar en el torneo de clausura 2014 de la LPL. También alcanzó un importante éxito internacional imponiéndose en el MSI 2015, con una serie 3-2 contra SKT T1. Además disfrutó de un récord de 14-2-6 en la temporada de verano 2015 de la LPL. A pesar de los éxitos alcanzados durante todo este tiempo como equipo, aún le queda lograr una importante marca en el Mundial. Esta vez entrará en la competencia más preparado que nunca, con algunos de los jugadores más celebrados y destacados del mundo. Ya tuvo oportunidad de disfrutar del primer lugar en la escena internacional en el MSI; ahora están ansiosos por repetir ese éxito en el Mundial.

Entrenador: Jung "RapidStar" Min-sung

bios.fr_FR: Pendant des années, LGD est restée coincée au milieu du classement des LPL. En dépit de quelques succès dans des tournois mineurs, ces joueurs n'ont pas menacé la domination d'EDG et de SHRC dans l'e-sport chinois. Puis LGD a décidé que ça suffisait comme ça. Elle a reconstruit l'équipe avec des joueurs coréens aguerris (imp, Flame et Acorn) à la fin de 2014. Les résultats parlent d'eux-mêmes : 1re place lors des play-offs d'été au LPL 2015.
bios.pl_PL: Od lat LGD znajduje się pośrodku tabeli LPL. Pomimo sukcesów w mniejszych turniejach nawet nie zbliżyło się do sukcesów EDG i SHRC w chińskim E-sporcie. I wtedy właśnie LGD stwierdziło, że starczy tego dobrego. Do swojego składu wcielili niezwykle utalentowanych Koreańczyków – impa, Flame'a i Acorna – pod koniec 2014 roku. Wyniki mówią same za siebie – 1. miejsce w letnich playoffach LPL 2015.
bios.de_DE: Seit Jahren steckte LGD in der Mitte der LPL-Tabelle fest. Trotz einigen Erfolgen bei kleineren Turnieren, schafften sie es nicht, die Dominanz von EDG oder SHRC zu beenden. Doch damit sollte nun ein für alle Mal Schluss sein. Sie verbesserten ihr Team mit den bekannten koreanischen Talenten imp, Flame und Acorn im Sommer 2014. Die Ergebnisse sprechen für sich - erster Platz der LPL Sommersaison in diesem Jahr.
bios.es_ES: LGD se pasó varios años estancado en centro de la tabla de la LPL. A pesar de obtener algunos éxitos en torneos menores, apenas alcanzó a mellar el férreo dominio que ejercían EDG o SHRC sobre los deportes electrónicos en China. Hasta que decidieron que ya estaba bien. A finales de 2014 reconstruyeron la plantilla con talentos coreanos de primera categoría, como Imp, Flame o Acorn. Los resultados hablan por sí mismos: Primer puesto de las eliminatorias de verano de la LPL 2015.
bios.pt_BR: A LGD passou anos vivendo na parte do meio da tabela LPL. Apesar de vitórias em alguns torneios menores, eles estavam longe de ameaçar a EDG ou a Royal Club no cenário chinês. Mas então eles deram um basta. Reconstruíram o time no final de 2014 com grandes astros coreanos: imp, Flame e Acorn. Os resultados falam por sisó -- campeões das eliminatórias de verão da LPL 2015.

bios.fr_FR: Invictus Gaming piaffe devant la porte de la gloire depuis si longtemps que l'équipe paraît presque frappée d'une malédiction. Au cours des deux dernières années, ils sont arrivés quatre fois 3e aux finales régionales ou aux play-offs de printemps de la LPL. Cependant, avec l'aide de joueurs dynamiques comme KaKAO et RooKie, Invictus va peut-être enfin briser la malédiction et parvenir au sommet.
bios.pl_PL: Invictus Gaming przez tak długo znajdowało się na krawędzi osiągnięcia sukcesu, że można pomyśleć, że drużyna jest przeklęta. Zajęli 3. miejsce podczas wiosennych playoffów LPL / finałów regionalnych 4 razy w ciągu ostatnich dwóch lat. Jednakże dzięki dołączeniu tak utalentowanych graczy, jak KaKAO i Rookie być może Invictus wreszcie przełamie klątwę i wywalczy sobie drogę na szczyt tabeli.
bios.de_DE: Invictus Gaming schwebte lange Zeit an der Grenze zum Erfolg, sodass es schien, sie seien verflucht. In zwei Jahren brachten sie viermal den dritten Platz in den LPL Spring Playoffs/Regional Finals nach Hause. Aber vielleicht schafft es diesmal Invictus, mit den dynamischen Talenten wie KaKAO und RooKie, den Fluch zu durchbrechen und sich den ganz Großen anzuschließen.
bios.es_ES: Invictus Gaming se ha quedado tantas veces a la puertas de la gloria que casi parece que están gafados. Han quedado en tercera posición en los Playoffs de primavera de la LPL y en las finales regionales de China cuatro veces en los dos últimos años. Aunque con los fichajes de los coreanos KaKAO y RooKie, quizás Invictus va a romper la maldición definitivamente y a hacerse un hueco entre los mejores equipos del mundo.
bios.pt_BR: A Invictus Gaming se aproximou da consagração tantas vezes, que até parece um time amaldiçoado. Eles ficaram em terceiro lugar nas Regionais e Eliminatórias da LPL quatro vezes nos últimos dois anos. Talvez agora, com a chegada de pequenos monstros como KaKAO e RooKie, eles consigam quebrar a maldição e chegar entre os grandes do Mundial.

bios.fr_FR: Snake a obtenu la 2e place lors de ses débuts dans la LPL lors de la compétition de printemps 2015. Ces débuts foudroyants se sont axés sur l'aptitude à miser toutes les ressources sur le carry AD et le top laner et à attendre les combats d'équipe de fin de partie pour faire basculer la partie en leur faveur. Ce n'est peut-être pas révolutionnaire, mais cela suffit pour permettre à Snake d'affronter les meilleures équipes de la LPL.
bios.pl_PL: Snake wyłoniło się z LSPL i zajęło 2. miejsce podczas swojego debiutu w LPL w wiosennym sezonie LPL 2015. Drużyna zademonstrowała chęć skupienia całej uwagi na swoim prowadzącym i górnym, a następnie wyczekania walk w późnej fazie gry, aby przechylić szalę zwycięstwa na swoją korzyść. Może nie jest to nic nowego, ale wystarczyło, aby utrzymać Snake w walce z najlepszymi drużynami w LPL.

Team WE są znani w chińskim e-sporcie od pradziejów. Jako pionierska organizacja e-sportowa zasłynęli w świecie ze swoich drużyn Warcrafta i StarCrafta, zanim w 2011 roku przestawili się na League of Legends. Po latach przeplatających się serii sukcesów i porażek Team WE w 2017 roku naprawdę się odnaleźli. Łącząc stare talenty z nowicjuszami, Team WE zdominowali wiosenny split LPL 2017, osiągając wynik 12–4 w fazie grupowej. Nie spoczęli na laurach i wkrótce przebili się przez konkurencję w play-offach, przegrywając tylko jedną grę w drodze po tytuł wiosennego splitu. Ich zwycięstwo 3–0 z Royal Never Give Up w finale stanowiło ukoronowanie znakomitego sezonu drużyny. Teraz szykują się do Rio, gdzie zamierzają wielokrotnie wykradać Barona oraz eliminować najlepsze drużyny świata na Mid-Season Invitational 2017. 

Trener: Namhoon „HooN” Kim
bios.es_ES:
Team WE es una vieja leyenda china de los esports. Como organización de esports pionera, ya era famosa mundialmente por sus equipos de Warcraft y Starcraft antes de que se uniera a League of Legends en 2011. Tras años alternando éxitos y fracasos, Team WE ha conseguido establecerse en 2017. Con una mezcla de viejos talentos y jugadores recién llegados, Team WE ha arrasado en el split de primavera de la LPL 2017, en la que batió un récord de 12 victorias frente a 4 derrotas en la fase de grupos. Pero la cosa no se quedó en eso. El equipo no tardaría en abrirse paso en los playoffs y en reclamar la corona del split de primavera con tan solo una derrota en su haber. Su resultado 3-0 en la final contra Royal Never Give Up es el colofón de una temporada estelar. Los jugadores de Team WE ahora se dirigen a Río y están preparados para robar el Barón y machacar a sus adversarios cuando se enfrenten a los mejores equipos del mundo en el Mid-Season Invitational 2017. 

Entrenador: Namhoon ''HooN'' Kim
bios.de_DE:
Team WE ist eine chinesische E-Sport-Legende, die so alt ist wie die Zeit selbst. Die E-Sport-Organisation gilt als Pionier auf diesem Gebiet und war für ihre Warcraft- und StarCraft-Mannschaften bekannt, bevor sie 2011 auf League of Legends umstieg. Nach Jahren voller Höhen und Tiefen scheint Team WE 2017 endlich einen guten Rhythmus gefunden zu haben. Dank einer Mischung aus alten Talenten und Neulingen konnte Team WE den Frühjahrs-Split der LPL dominieren und beendete die Gruppenphase mit 12 Siegen bei nur 4 Niederlagen. Doch das war ihnen noch nicht genug. Sie marschierten durch die Entscheidungsspiele und verloren auf dem Weg zum Titel nur ein einziges Spiel. Die Krönung ihrer sensationellen Saison war der 3–0 Sieg über Royal Never Give Up im Finale des Frühjahrs-Splits. Jetzt konzentrieren sie sich ganz auf Rio, wo sie den ein oder anderen Baron stehlen und ihre Gegner aufmischen wollen, wenn sie sich beim Mid-Season Invitational 2017 mit den besten Mannschaften der Welt messen. 

Trainer: Namhoon „HooN“ Kim
bios.pt_BR:
A história da Team WE nos e-Sports chineses é tão antiga quanto o tempo. Como uma organização pioneira na área de e-Sports, eles já haviam alcançado renome internacional com suas equipes de Warcraft e Starcraft quando fizeram o salto para League of Legends em 2011. Após passar anos intercalando sucessos e fracassos, a Team WE encontrou de vez o seu caminho em 2017. Misturando talentos experientes com novatos promissores, a Team WE dominou a Etapa de Primavera da LPL 2017 com um recorde de 12-4 na fase de grupos. Sem parar por aí, eles logo abriram caminho entre a competição das eliminatórias, perdendo apenas um jogo na sua jornada até a coroa da Etapa de Primavera. A surra de 3-0 que deram na Royal Never Give Up na final colocou um ponto de exclamação na sua já extraordinária temporada. Agora, seu foco está no Rio e eles pretendem roubar Barões e mostrar a que vieram em seus confrontos contra as melhores equipes do mundo no Mid-Season Invitational 2017.

Técnico: Namhoon “HooN” Kim
bios.es_AR: El Team WE es un cuento de Esports tan viejo como el tiempo. Como una organización pionera de Esports, se volvieron conocidos internacionalmente por sus equipos de Warcraft y Starcraft antes de entrar a LoL en el 2011. Después de años de éxitos y fracasos, el Team WE encontró su ritmo en 2017. Al mezclar talento viejo con nuevo, el Team WE dominó el Torneo de Apertura LPL de 2017 y alcanzó un récord de 12-4 en la fase de grupos. No se detuvieron ahí. En cuanto llegaron a las eliminatorias solo perdieron una partida en su camino a la victoria del Torneo de Apertura. Su aplastante 3-0 en el Royal Never Give Up en las finales fue la cereza del pastel en su temporada. Ahora tienen los ojos puestos en Río y están listos para robar barones y aplastar a sus oponentes cuando se enfrenten a los mejores equipos del mundo en el Mid-Season Invitational 2017.

Royal Never Give Up ha sido uno de los equipos más fuertes de China en los últimos años. Consiguieron múltiples posiciones número 1, como locales, en la LPL e incluso alcanzaron la fase eliminatoria del Torneo por Invitación de Temporada del 2016. El equipo ha cultivado algunos de los más grandes talentos en China y han construido una fuerte alineación con experiencia, talento y tenacidad. Como los segundos clasificados de China, RNG representará a sus simpatizantes dentro del mayor escenario existente. Con esta alineación y su historia, no tenemos la menor duda de que podrán cumplir con la tarea.

Entrenador: Kim "Fly" Sang-chul
bios.fr_FR: Royal Never Give Up a emprunté la voie royale et remporté les LPL printemps 2016 lors de son second segment, en triomphant de plusieurs équipes telles que Qiao Gu Reapers, Edward Gaming et Team World Elite. Désormais au même niveau que son homologue Star Horn Royal Club, deux fois finaliste du Championnat du monde, l'organisation Royale n'est pas étrangère au succès sur la scène internationale. Après avoir goûté à la compétition internationale en arrivant en 3e/4e place de l'IEM Season X World Championship, l'équipe va tenter de transposer son succès national sur la scène mondiale.
bios.es_ES: Royal Never Give Up ha sido uno de los equipos más fuertes del último año en China. Se hicieron con varios primeros puestos en la LPL y, además, llegaron a la fase eliminatoria del MSI 2016. El equipo ha dado lugar a algunos de los mayores talentos de China y ha construido un buen plantel con experiencia, talento y tenacidad. Como segundo clasificado de China, RNG representará a sus seguidores en el mayor escenario posible. Con esta plantilla y con su historial, no hay duda de que cumplirán lo que prometen.
bios.de_DE: Royal Never Give Up war im vergangenen Jahr eine der stärksten Mannschaften Chinas. Sie konnten in der LPL mehrere erste Plätze erobern und erreichten sogar die K.-o.-Phase des Mid-Season Invitational 2016. Die Mannschaft hat ein paar der größten Talente Chinas hervorgebracht und verfügt über eine starke Aufstellung voller Erfahrung, Talent und Entschlossenheit. RNG konnte sich als zweite chinesische Mannschaft für die WM qualifizieren und wird versuchen, ihre Fans auf der größten aller Bühnen zu begeistern. Dank ihrer Aufstellung und ihrer Geschichte haben wir keinen Zweifel daran, dass sie für diese Aufgabe gewappnet sind.
bios.pl_PL: Royal Never Give Up zwyciężyli w wiosennym LPL 2016 podczas swojego drugiego splitu, pokonując takie drużyny, jak Qiao Gu Reapers, Edward Gaming oraz Team World Elite. Będąca przeciwieństwem dwukrotnych finalistów Mistrzostw Świata Star Horn Royal Club, organizacja Royal jest za pan brat z sukcesami na międzynarodowej scenie. Po zasmakowaniu międzynarodowej rywalizacji, zajmując miejsce 3./4. podczas Mistrzostw Świata 10. sezonu IEM, będą chcieli odtworzyć swój krajowy sukces za granicą.
bios.pt_BR: A Royal Never Give Up foi uma das equipes mais fortes da China no ano passado. Eles abocanharam vários primeiros lugares na LPL e também chegaram à fase eliminatória do MSI 2016. A equipe produziu alguns dos maiores talentos da China e compôs um elenco forte, experiente, talentoso e obstinado. Como a segunda melhor equipe da China, a RNG vai representar sua torcida de fãs no maior palco que existe. E com esse elenco e esse histórico, não temos dúvidas de que eles vão dar conta do recado.

bios.de_DE: I MAY ist ein Name, der Hoffnung ausstrahlt. Und das passt zum Ursprung dieser Mannschaft. IM war ursprünglich die zweite Mannschaft von Edward Gaming in der LSPL – ein bescheidener Anfang für eine Mannschaft, die jetzt zur WM fährt. Die Mannschaft, die damals noch als EDE bekannt war, gewann die LSPL und trat als I MAY beim Sommer-Split der LPL an. Ihr Erfolgslauf setzte sich im Sommer-Split fort und gipfelte in einem 3–2 Sieg über Team WE, mit dem sie sich für die Weltmeisterschaft qualifizierten. IM hat es allen Zweiflern und Kritikern gezeigt, die sich sichern waren, dass sie wegen ihres knappen Aufstiegs in die LPL niemals das höchste spielerische Niveau erreichen würden. Doch IM ließ sich von dieser Einschätzung nicht abschrecken und konnte in den Schlüsselmomenten Siege einfahren. Jetzt fährt die Mannschaft zur größten Bühne von League, um herauszufinden, ob sie mit ihrer verwegenen Art weitere überraschende Siege einfahren können.
bios.es_AR:
I MAY es un nombre que denota esperanza, más que nada si se tiene en cuenta el origen de este equipo. IM comenzó en la LSPL como el segundo equipo de Edward Gaming, y sus comienzos fueron bastante humildes para ser un equipo que esté camino al Mundial. El equipo, conocido como EDE, logró salir del LSPL con un boleto al torneo de clausura de la LPL y bajo el nombre de I MAY. Su maravillosa actuación continuó a lo largo del torneo de clausura y terminó con una victoria por 3-2 contra Team WE y un pase al Campeonato Mundial. IM despejó las dudas de los escépticos y los críticos que sugerían que su casual ascenso a la LPL demostraba que nunca lograrían llegar a los más altos niveles de competición. Sin dejarse llevar por estos comentarios, IM continuó con su perfil bajo y obteniendo victorias en momentos clave. Ahora deberán saborear el escenario más grande de League of Legends y ver si pueden continuar con su audaz empresa de obtener más victorias de estas inesperadas.

Entrenador: Son "Kezman" Dae-young
bios.pt_BR: I MAY, "eu posso" em inglês, é um nome que irradia esperança e reflete as origens do time. A IM começou na LSPL com o segundo time da Edward Gaming -- começo humilde para uma equipe que agora vai para o Mundial. A equipe, antes conhecida como EDE, conseguiu sair da LSPL e chegou à Etapa de Verão da LPL como I MAY. Sua jornada de sucesso continuou até a Etapa de Verão, culminando com a classificação para o Mundial com uma vitória por 3 a 2 contra a WE. A IM calou a boca dos críticos e céticos que sugeriam que sua disputada ascensão à LPL era a prova de que eles não conseguiriam chegar aos níveis mais altos da competição. Sem temer essa percepção, a IM manteve a cabeça erguida e continuou vencendo em momentos cruciais. Agora chegou a hora da equipe vivenciar o nível máximo de League e ver se consegue dar continuidade a ousada tendência de abocanhar vitórias surpreendentes.
